Top Gun: Maverick is the upcoming sequel to the 1986 film Top Gun. The movie follows the story of Pete "Maverick" Mitchell, who is now a flight instructor and still pushing the envelope as a courageous test pilot. Maverick mentors a new generation of U.S. Navy fighter pilots, including Bradley Bradshaw, the son of Maverick's late friend and Radar Intercept Officer, Nick "Goose" Bradshaw. Maverick navigates the changing times and learns to confront his own past mistakes, while also facing unexpected challenges and threats that put the future of the program in jeopardy. As Maverick works to honor the legacy of those who came before him and forge a new path forward, he finds himself drawn to a civilian woman named Penny Benjamin, who becomes a key figure in his journey. Ultimately, Maverick must confront his deepest fears and take on a mission that will require him to risk everything to prove that he is still the best of the best.